Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.73,0:00:07.56,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It has been roughly one century since the Apollo moon landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.64,0:00:14.15,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Humanity's first exploration ship to Jupiter, the Von Braun, is preparing to set sail,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.41,0:00:19.05,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...carrying with it humanity's hopes and dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.09,0:00:29.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you done yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.52,0:00:31.48,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.79,0:00:37.67,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hakim Ashmead was a member of the Space Defense Front.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.97,0:00:44.79,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,His goal all along was to take the crew test to get a shot at the Von Braun.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.71,0:00:50.47,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You remember that terrorist attack where they tried to slam...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.47,0:00:53.05,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...that communications satellite into ISPV-7, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.41,0:00:55.22,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Based on our investigation, we've learned he had been...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.22,0:00:57.91,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...leaking them information from the OSA in that incident, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.29,0:01:02.25,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He was working as a terrorist the whole time he was in the OSA.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.82,0:01:07.18,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's been at large ever since his attempt to destroy the Von Braun failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.49,0:01:09.41,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We believe that he is on the moon.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.87,0:01:08.90,Alternative (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.00,0:01:12.95,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We'd like you to tell us everything that you know about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.76,0:01:13.74,Alternative (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(352,418)}Why couldn't I think of one for him?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.49,0:01:16.44,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's your duty as a fellow member of the OSA.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.96,0:01:18.04,Alternative (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why couldn't I come up with a nickname?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.81,0:02:58.23,F.O. (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\move(630,368,420,355)\fad(760,830)\bord0.1\shad2\fs20\fscx100\fscy100\t(\fs28\fscx100\fscy100)}Exposure
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.20,0:03:00.77,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why am I being taken off the flight?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.18,0:03:03.44,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Standard procedure is to have the same crew on the flight out and back again, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.81,0:03:04.74,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't make any sense!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.01,0:03:07.05,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What it means is, go cool your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.38,0:03:10.91,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what's gotten you so angry, but you've been acting strange lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.94,0:03:12.45,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Strange?! Strange how?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.48,0:03:17.06,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This. This right here. You never used to raise your voice like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.30,0:03:21.65,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The way you're acting now, I can't trust you with other people's lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.13,0:03:24.28,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's the call I've made as the ship's captain.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.87,0:03:26.29,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Go relearn your job on a freighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.76,0:03:27.30,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.92,0:03:48.87,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It was my decision, wasn't it?\NWhat's the point of talking it over with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.42,0:03:51.35,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have my own life.\NAnd you have your own, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.73,0:03:56.28,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is most ridiculous, Tanabe.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.83,0:04:00.39,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The paperwork has become quite complicated thanks to the INTO Supreme Council meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.00,0:04:04.03,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds like the shuttle carrying the Chief and the others is going to be a little late,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.61,0:04:06.72,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...so you can go ahead and take off early.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.48,0:04:10.18,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tanabe?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.03,0:04:13.39,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.52,0:04:17.23,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Did you try calling the security company?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.23,0:04:19.85,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They said that everyone is out handling security for the Supreme Council meeting!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.92,0:04:21.93,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You got 30 for us? Great!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.93,0:04:24.15,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I think we can make do with these prices here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.13,0:04:29.08,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hard to believe that this is the management company...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.08,0:04:31.62,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...that's running the Jupiter project that humanity is pinning its future on.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.62,0:04:33.95,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Because we can't spare any time to worry about how we look.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.47,0:04:38.60,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This may be the Jupiter project, but it's not a high-priority item inside INTO.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.31,0:04:42.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The budget is as large as you'd expect,\N but most of the money has strings attached.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.63,0:04:44.28,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hardly any funds in the budget are discretionary.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.98,0:04:47.61,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, I plan to cut the majority of those strings...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.02,0:04:51.63,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I like that look on your face, Dolf.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.05,0:04:56.98,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're definitely cut out out for playing\NDavid to somebody else's Goliath.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.48,0:05:01.08,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You came here to ask about that Hoshino-kun, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.33,0:05:05.94,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The people taking the third round of tests are effectively incommunicado.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.54,0:05:07.45,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're worried, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.76,0:05:09.99,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really care about the test results one way or the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.99,0:05:12.19,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm more worried about the girl he's going out with.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.54,0:05:14.36,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're a good leader.\NYou care about your people.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.36,0:05:15.29,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So are you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.29,0:05:17.37,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Just give them some spiel about improving their image.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.62,0:05:20.84,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Chad looks like a whole new man compared to when he was at Technora.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.28,0:05:23.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't intend to let any of\N my valuable resources sit and rot.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.12,0:05:27.95,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I regret that I let that happen. And that\NI didn't use Debris Section properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.59,0:05:37.40,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Even if he passed a difficult test,\N he's still a failure as a human being.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.93,0:05:40.98,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now I think I understand why you broke up with him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.87,0:05:43.18,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's a good look for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.61,0:05:46.35,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You have a nice face and body, you've got a good head on your shoulders,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.87,0:05:49.08,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and to top it all off, you come from a wealthy family and you have a good personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.81,0:05:51.78,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,To tell you the truth, I always thought you were too good to be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.71,0:05:55.91,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're awfully mean-spirited today, Claire.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.52,0:06:00.35,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You never knew, did you?\NI hated you with every fiber of my being.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.99,0:06:05.94,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You see yourself as a considerate man.\N That's horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.23,0:06:07.23,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.86,0:06:11.25,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You think you're sensitive, but you're awfully dense where it really counts.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.93,0:06:14.76,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know the first thing about me or Hachi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.70,0:06:16.87,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You can never really know someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.43,0:06:21.39,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Claire Rondo, employed with the Debris\NSection of Technora's Second Division?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.08,0:06:23.99,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Would you mind coming with us to the Orbital Security Agency?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.75,0:06:25.72,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.51,0:06:29.20,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't get the wrong impression.\NThis is purely voluntary.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.49,0:06:32.78,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Would you agree to come in if I said that it was about Hakim Ashmead?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.12,0:06:34.79,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All right, I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.59,0:06:42.70,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There are lots and lots of dark, dirty secrets in this world that you don't know anything about.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.71,0:06:48.13,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Sea of Tranquility Office of\NDevelopment Promotion has...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.89,0:06:51.78,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the people from Second Division are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.37,0:06:54.35,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, the Debris Section reinforcements.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.61,0:06:56.61,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, they're taking the elevator up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.41,0:07:00.98,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if this is gonna work out?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.98,0:07:04.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to be working\N together for at least a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.02,0:07:07.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be fine! Debris Sections are the\N lowest performers in every division.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.92,0:07:09.23,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As departments go, we're all dead weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.27,0:07:12.91,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but they're on Level B. That's three floors above the reception desk!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.29,0:07:15.26,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Our office is way down in a basement storage room!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.32,0:07:17.30,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Stop worrying so much, Chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.33,0:07:19.75,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I brought along the perfect gag to break the ice!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.20,0:07:20.88,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.51,0:07:26.72,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world is that supposed to be?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.75,0:07:29.17,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it great?\NIt'll go over like gangbusters!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.38,0:07:32.75,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If they asked me to, I could even be the opening act for the Supreme Council meeting!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.01,0:07:33.50,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.08,0:07:37.80,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is this really their Debris Section?\NIt's so neat and tidy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.12,0:07:41.20,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe we really should've brought along our field team, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.36,0:07:42.64,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Or at least an introductory gift...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.02,0:07:44.74,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We'd be late if we went and bought something now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.81,0:07:48.38,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tidy offices like this are always sticklers for punctuality, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.38,0:07:51.08,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll go buy something myself!\NYou go on without me, Chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.43,0:07:54.73,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to go in alone!\NI'll go buy the gift!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.76,0:07:56.74,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn't possibly ask you to run an errand, Chief!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.77,0:07:58.24,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, no! I'll do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.24,0:07:59.16,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, I will!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.16,0:07:59.99,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Get moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.26,0:08:04.67,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.65,0:08:13.31,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome to Debris Section!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.76,0:08:18.05,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,C-Chief?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.60,0:08:23.05,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A hearty welcome to all our friends from the Second Division!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.60,0:08:26.27,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I guess Debris Sectons are\N Debris Sections no matter where you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.94,0:08:33.74,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He maintained a top-class record ever since he joined the OSA.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.31,0:08:37.36,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He won the Jim Lovell Award in 2073.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.91,0:08:41.37,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hakim Ashmead was an exemplary member of the OSA.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.88,0:08:43.67,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,His circle of social aquaintances was broad, but shallow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.99,0:08:46.66,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He was even careful enough to be involved in Greenhouse Effect Prevention activism.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.00,0:08:50.36,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,On the surface, he was a proponent of space development.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.89,0:08:51.87,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He had everyone totally...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.00,0:09:01.07,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hoshino Hachirota-san,\N thank you for your cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.67,0:09:05.08,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're free to go now.\NPick up your belongings at the front desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.67,0:09:07.63,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Also, this matter isn't to be discussed with anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.04,0:09:10.11,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible that your family might be put at risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.11,0:09:11.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I know, I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.55,0:09:13.37,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can get back to my testing now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.62,0:09:15.95,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As for that, please wait until we contact you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.85,0:09:22.48,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Claire?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.46,0:09:25.87,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What're you...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.21,0:09:27.38,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're worried about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.88,0:09:30.54,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right. For the moment,\NI'm cooperating voluntarily.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.83,0:09:31.49,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.89,0:09:35.66,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They think that I'm a member of the Space Defense Front.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.97,0:09:36.51,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.89,0:09:39.37,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What're you guys talking about?\NThat's the stupidest thing I've ever heard!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.39,0:09:40.16,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hoshino-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.17,0:09:41.72,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She'd never do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.98,0:09:44.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's because I'm Hakim Ashmead's girlfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.48,0:09:47.45,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's what you think, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.06,0:09:50.69,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let's talk about the details in the interview room, all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.15,0:09:51.80,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.30,0:09:53.01,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Does that bother you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.03,0:09:53.67,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Of course it does!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.04,0:09:55.62,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You have Tanabe-san, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.36,0:10:01.32,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No one ever fully commits with their feelings...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.30,0:10:07.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Again, everything we discussed is to remain confidential.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.63,0:10:08.23,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.61,0:10:21.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, humans are all alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.82,0:10:24.05,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You have your own life, and other people have their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.62,0:10:26.30,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You said the same thing to Tanabe, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.00,0:10:29.01,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So why are you so pissed off at Hakim for?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.96,0:10:32.87,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Basically, you were pinning your hopes on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.23,0:10:35.83,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You wanted somebody who would make the trip to Jupiter with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.50,0:10:39.30,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Cheng-Shin couldn't have done it.\NBut Hakim, he could've.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.78,0:10:41.25,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Gee, that's too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.67,0:10:44.24,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And just when you thought you'd made yourself a friend, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.84,0:10:46.77,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When it's all said and done, people are alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.47,0:10:49.83,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Even those stars that seem to be packed shoulder to shoulder in the night sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.28,0:10:52.38,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...are actually separated by vast distances.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.21,0:10:58.93,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In between those stars, there's nothing but dark, cold, cruel space.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.79,0:11:03.52,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.12,0:11:06.93,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing, I just thought that\NI saw someone I knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.24,0:11:22.11,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What am I, some kind of moron?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.86,0:11:23.62,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How can I talk to her now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.99,0:11:26.32,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.15,0:11:29.22,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, your name's...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.44,0:11:31.44,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Um, it's Tarobo.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.63,0:11:33.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Right, that was your name...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.51,0:11:35.00,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where are the other ninjas?\NAre they around?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.00,0:11:38.58,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry!\NPlease, pretend you didn't see this!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.79,0:11:41.38,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have a job, so I don't have any money...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.76,0:11:43.59,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So please... Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.70,0:11:46.55,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They're all dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.20,0:11:48.52,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone but me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.55,0:11:52.64,F.O. (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnbolide\fs16\fscy130\bord0\shad0\c&H92927D&\pos(352,254)\frz1}Matter is void, all is vanity
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.63,0:11:49.11,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They're dead?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.81,0:11:52.34,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They had gotten jobs working on the tandem mirror engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.07,0:11:58.61,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Back during that hotel fire,\NI was the only one who was afraid...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.91,0:12:04.33,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since, we've had a bit of a falling out.\NThey didn't ask me to come along to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.32,0:12:11.29,F.O. (PlanetES),,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnbolide\bord0\shad0\c&H62574B&\pos(358,287)}Matter is void, all is vanity
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.02,0:12:07.48,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, what were you doing in here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.60,0:12:17.96,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You were selling off their stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.88,0:12:25.57,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.57,0:12:26.35,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.67,0:12:29.67,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I don't expect any better from human beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.89,0:12:42.44,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess I can come up with some way to make the deadline,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.31,0:12:47.28,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...but don't make any more sudden changes to the schedule, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.58,0:12:51.32,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Moving up the schedule and taking the ship down into lunar orbit...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.47,0:12:53.16,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...was a request on the part of our sponsor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.40,0:12:54.74,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't make any promises in that regard.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.99,0:12:58.82,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, it's so obvious that they wanna show off to the media.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.21,0:13:02.56,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"The first Supreme Council meeting in space,"\N my ass...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.91,0:13:07.25,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, and when's the captain coming? I heard that you're gonna be staying behind on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.79,0:13:11.44,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The President says that he'll arrive when the people who passed the test are announced.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.75,0:13:14.39,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oops.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.72,0:13:16.23,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You said that you've had that hook for many years, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.86,0:13:20.44,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I've been using this ever since my first flight to Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.43,0:13:24.26,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I was with Gigalt on that trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.95,0:13:48.65,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,With the historic first meeting of the Supreme\NCouncil to be held here in two days,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.05,0:13:51.80,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...the atmosphere here at the lunar station is tense.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.96,0:13:55.00,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like Chairman Clifford has arrived!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.67,0:13:57.27,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He is surrounded by his bodyguards!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.66,0:14:00.05,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Look at that! He's waving cheerfully at the press corps!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.35,0:14:01.93,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Moving the meeting from Sea of Tranquility City to the lunar station was a drastic measure.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.43,0:14:04.83,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need to go all the way down to the lunar surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.83,0:14:08.01,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All that matters is that we held the meeting in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.34,0:14:08.65,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.12,0:14:10.93,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose that it's also easier to beef up security here,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.41,0:14:14.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and it's probably also forced those terrorists to change their plans.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.71,0:14:19.21,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The number of security personnel on the lunar station is nearly triple what it was a month ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.62,0:14:22.50,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,On the other hand, security in Sea of\NTranquility City is now short-handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.50,0:14:27.23,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,73% of the OSA's patrol vessels are gathered in lunar orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.80,0:14:30.76,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...checking out every satellite and piece of debris that they come across.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.10,0:14:35.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like our recent operation against\NISPV-7 had an effect on them.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.46,0:14:38.42,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It's made our work here much easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.81,0:14:43.56,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The work on Catnip is finished. They say it can cover all of lunar orbit for 40 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.01,0:14:45.19,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How about the Black Cats?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.68,0:14:49.19,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We've gathered six.\NWe think we can get one or two more.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.69,0:14:51.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Tiger has begun its descent into lunar orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.22,0:14:53.55,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Everything is going according to plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.33,0:14:55.37,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't do anything to raise their suspicions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.82,0:14:59.71,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,With our inferior numbers, our only chance of victory is with a sneak attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.17,0:15:07.66,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'll be! It's Hachimaki!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.66,0:15:10.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What're you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.42,0:15:11.05,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.50,0:15:13.27,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ha-chan! Long time, no see!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.00,0:15:16.67,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We heard that you've made it all the way to the third round of testing!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.94,0:15:19.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This joker is a fellow debris hauler!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.31,0:15:21.23,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He passed the test for the Von Braun!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.08,0:15:25.68,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's all thanks to my guidance, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.69,0:15:27.00,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't that right, Hachi?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.49,0:15:33.08,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hoshino-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.66,0:15:36.24,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tanabe-san is working hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.83,0:15:40.30,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She said that she'll do the job right even if you aren't there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.84,0:15:42.32,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That she'd give it her best even on her own.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.33,0:15:45.45,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hachi! Stop by the office sometime!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.64,0:15:47.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You've got a lot of mail piling up!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.21,0:15:50.96,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You don't need to worry about the work-related stuff, but there's some personal e-mails, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.21,0:15:52.38,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We're sorry, Ha-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.71,0:15:55.72,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We took the liberty of looking through them to make sure there wasn't anything urgent.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.32,0:15:58.44,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's okay.\NWho were the e-mails from?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.79,0:16:02.06,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They're mostly from Maintence and Records, so they're probably from your dorm buddies.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.39,0:16:04.20,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There was one from Gigalt-san, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.52,0:16:05.99,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,From Sensei? What did it say?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.53,0:16:09.91,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It said to come to Sea of Tranquility Medical\NCenter once you were done with your tests.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.50,0:16:11.09,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The hospital?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.49,0:16:28.99,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wanna read this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.54,0:16:33.65,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's this week's Cosmonauts.\NI already read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.49,0:16:36.91,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Hachimaki.\NGetting a check-up?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.35,0:16:38.75,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm here to visit somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.44,0:16:41.22,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Gigalt-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.89,0:16:42.68,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You know him?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.43,0:16:43.90,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.39,0:16:46.26,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He taught me all I know about EVA.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.62,0:16:48.52,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's the kind of guy who's too tough to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.90,0:16:50.57,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I guess he's getting on in years if he's in the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.16,0:16:54.36,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,His e-mail said to come see him once I was finished with testing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.72,0:16:55.68,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know which room he's in?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.94,0:17:06.35,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Here. Gigalt-san said to give this to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.16,0:17:11.63,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What, Sensei's not around anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.19,0:17:13.59,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No. He's gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.29,0:17:16.88,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, that's one spry old geezer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.22,0:17:19.39,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Did he give you a weird nickname, Nono?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.62,0:17:21.48,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hachimaki, what I meant was...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.74,0:17:24.62,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Nono-chan, it's time for your check-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.06,0:17:25.84,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.41,0:17:28.66,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have the day off, so I'll wait for you until you're done.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.18,0:17:29.90,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You will?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.22,0:17:31.98,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What? You ran into Senpai?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.35,0:17:34.98,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yep, we ran smack into him on our way back from our first round of bar hopping...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.18,0:17:37.76,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ai-chan! Come join us for round two!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.98,0:17:39.71,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Will you come? C'mon over!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.02,0:17:41.43,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's that? Where did he go?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.99,0:17:44.50,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Beats me, maybe he went back to his place.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.19,0:17:47.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Lavie-chan! You remember!\NHe went to what's-it-called...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.49,0:17:48.95,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. It's me, dammit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.13,0:17:50.70,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Edel?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.23,0:17:51.69,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.23,0:17:53.15,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you drunk?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.43,0:17:55.33,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I've had 12 single malt doubles.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.88,0:17:57.34,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But that's not important, he's at the hospital!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.10,0:18:00.18,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That bozo Hachi's at Sea of\NTranquility Medical Center!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.57,0:18:02.40,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you leave now, you can still catch him there!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.11,0:18:05.59,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,From where you are, the fastest way is to go up to the first floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.59,0:18:07.35,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and take the shuttle bus from the spaceport!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.31,0:18:10.70,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you run, you can still make the 7:47 bus! Get moving!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.18,0:18:12.70,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Edel.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.24,0:18:46.96,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Living alone and dying alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.75,0:18:48.55,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.66,0:18:51.40,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How could anyone be satisfied with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.26,0:18:53.06,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's stupid...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.54,0:19:07.94,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, that's Sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.61,0:19:12.92,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a long time, Hachimaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.58,0:19:19.16,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you're watching this video,\N it means that I'm probably dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.49,0:19:26.37,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's cancer. Well, for us astronauts, it's like an occupational hazard.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.87,0:19:30.02,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I guess that's the kind of place that space is. You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.02,0:19:39.38,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that Harry Rowland, my own Sensei, died here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.25,0:19:41.78,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Space is such a cold place...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.28,0:19:44.91,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And it's cruel. And it's heartless.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.87,0:19:48.04,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But we fall in love with her, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.39,0:19:51.98,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Like a pure-hearted boy falling for a bad girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.15,0:19:55.96,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I guess this is what they mean by loving something, warts and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.13,0:20:04.51,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So anyway, what's this I hear about you taking the test for the Von Braun?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.53,0:20:06.97,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I heard about it from Hakim.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.57,0:20:10.24,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's a tough guy, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.97,0:20:12.81,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He'll make a good rival for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.20,0:20:14.59,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh. One more thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.44,0:20:18.06,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I've got one last lesson to teach you.\NIt's very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.02,0:20:20.70,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Every ship needs a harbor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.17,0:20:24.73,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They need a harbor that will always be there waiting for them,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.73,0:20:27.46,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and will take them in when they finally arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.70,0:20:29.55,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.15,0:20:33.08,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, give my best to Goro.\NWe'd both get all maudlin.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.93,0:20:35.00,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I want you two to try to get along.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.00,0:20:43.43,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who's there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.74,0:20:45.48,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.04,0:20:53.16,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Paging Niide-sensei of the outpatient clinic.\N Paging Niide-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.43,0:20:55.42,Other (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please come to the pharmacy immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.38,0:20:59.15,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.92,0:21:01.86,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank goodness! I've been looking everywhere for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.32,0:21:03.79,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I had to see you and talk to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.51,0:21:07.93,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone's worried about you. You haven't called, so we didn't know how you were doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.00,0:21:12.69,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Um, Senpai...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.57,0:21:17.47,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That was a lie, right?\NAbout being okay with being alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.04,0:21:19.88,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Life's too lonely to go through it all alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.01,0:21:21.79,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sensei, he's...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.44,0:21:24.68,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Gigalt Sensei is...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.30,0:21:27.32,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He can't be! He said he was still fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.59,0:21:30.13,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Still"?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.70,0:21:32.60,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tanabe, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.10,0:21:39.69,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know about this?\NYou knew Sensei had cancer?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.27,0:21:41.84,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.99,0:21:45.11,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You knew, and you didn't say anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.08,0:21:46.78,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.98,0:21:51.61,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,See, it's just like I said.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.63,0:21:55.74,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,People say they like you and they love you, but this is what they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.41,0:22:01.58,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Gigalt-san said that he didn't want me to say anything to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.83,0:22:05.16,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But that's just an excuse, I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.67,0:22:07.61,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,People, stars, there's no difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.19,0:22:10.89,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They just float there, all alone in the vastness of space.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.29,0:22:12.88,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Senpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.57,0:22:17.48,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I bet you're feeling sad, hurt, and angry...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.95,0:22:23.32,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing but cold, cruel, dark space between you and Tanabe, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.31,0:22:28.70,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But I think that you can make things like that a little easier to bear by sharing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.48,0:22:31.88,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Something that might be too hard to bear alone might be easier with two people...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.42,0:22:36.05,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And you're gonna realize that you're gonna die alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.98,0:22:38.38,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Just like Gigalt.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.38,0:22:38.96,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.46,0:22:40.63,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Shut the hell up!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.46,0:22:43.84,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's all mine!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.32,0:22:48.62,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All the loneliness! All the pain!\NAll the doubts! All the regrets!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.17,0:22:52.59,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You don't deserve them!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.60,0:23:00.52,Standard (PlanetES),Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,4437)}No way in hell am I gonna give 'em away to you!
